{
  "text": "However, another study demonstrated favorable fruit intake among limited English speaking Hispanics at 1.21 times per day versus 0.98 times per day among non-Hispanic Blacks [CITATION_1] . Despite indications that consumption may be higher for Hispanics, this subgroup, along with other health disparate populations, are not meeting dietary guidelines. Thus, strategies are needed to increase fruit and vegetable intake among Hispanics.",
